WEBVTT

00:01.958 --> 00:04.265
My husband is missing!
What have you done with him?

00:04.395 --> 00:05.396
I assure you, ma'am,
I don't know

00:05.527 --> 00:08.660
who or where your husband is.

00:08.791 --> 00:11.315
I'm afraid you'll find few
friends in Preacher's Corners.

00:11.446 --> 00:12.490
[Sam] They practically
threw a parade

00:12.621 --> 00:14.362
when your cousin
hanged himself.

00:14.492 --> 00:17.582
Stephen's daughter, Marcella,
meant everything to him.

00:17.713 --> 00:20.455
She fell down the cellar stairs.
Broke her back into pieces.

00:20.585 --> 00:22.761
Let's send these
new Boones packing

00:22.892 --> 00:25.503
before they inflict
their own wickedness on us.

00:25.634 --> 00:26.330
Burn it then.

00:27.418 --> 00:28.419
No!

00:28.550 --> 00:29.725
Where are my shells?

00:29.855 --> 00:31.292
Tane, those were Mom's shells.

00:31.422 --> 00:32.336
If you're playing a game
on Loa, it's not--

00:32.467 --> 00:33.381
I didn't take 'em!

00:33.511 --> 00:34.686
I'm a little tired.

00:34.817 --> 00:36.210
[husband]
Are you running a fever?

00:36.340 --> 00:37.037
[wife] It's not the illness.

00:38.995 --> 00:40.866
[Fletcher] I didn't see
no crappin's, no holes.

00:40.997 --> 00:42.825
Just a couple
of dried-up carcasses.

00:42.955 --> 00:45.393
[Charles] Well, we have rats,
Mr. Fletcher, I assure you.

00:46.611 --> 00:48.526
[Mrs. Cloris]
This is a sad house, Captain.

00:48.657 --> 00:50.354
No Boone has ever been
happy here.

00:50.485 --> 00:52.356
[gasps]

00:52.487 --> 00:56.317
There's something inside
that you hide from us.

00:56.447 --> 00:58.362
[gasps, groans]

00:58.493 --> 01:00.843
It scares me.

01:00.973 --> 01:02.453
- [man] What happened here?
- [Rose] Edward!

01:02.584 --> 01:03.715
[Dr. Guilford]
Susan Mallory passed.

01:03.846 --> 01:05.326
[Rose] It was a Boone!

01:05.456 --> 01:06.588
Stephen Boone killed my baby!

01:06.718 --> 01:07.763
Clearly this woman needs help.

01:07.893 --> 01:09.852
- Dig him up!
- Prove it.

01:09.982 --> 01:11.723
[Charles] If you all believe
this is true,

01:11.854 --> 01:13.203
then there really is
no hope for this town.

01:37.009 --> 01:42.102
♪♪♪

02:14.046 --> 02:19.617
♪♪♪

03:17.153 --> 03:19.808
[theme music plays]

03:19.938 --> 03:25.814
♪♪♪

05:15.097 --> 05:16.925
[Stephen's voice]
Dear Cousin Charles,

05:17.055 --> 05:18.970
By the time you receive
this letter

05:19.101 --> 05:21.756
I shall be
in my final resting place.

05:21.886 --> 05:23.801
Our fathers
went to their graves

05:23.932 --> 05:26.630
as bitter enemies
over a property dispute.

05:26.761 --> 05:30.155
I do not wish us
the same fate, dear cousin.

05:30.286 --> 05:33.289
I believe your father
was swindled by mine.

05:33.420 --> 05:35.073
As restitution
for my father's sin,

05:35.204 --> 05:37.598
I bequeath you,
Charles Boone,

05:37.728 --> 05:39.861
my sole heir
and last blood relation

05:39.991 --> 05:41.863
with all that I own:

05:41.993 --> 05:43.778
namely,
a prosperous timber mill

05:43.908 --> 05:45.997
and all
its associated acreage,

05:46.128 --> 05:48.739
and lastly,
a magnificent ancestral home

05:48.870 --> 05:51.002
we call Chapelwaite.

05:51.133 --> 05:52.439
- Father?
- [startles]

05:54.702 --> 05:56.007
Yes?

05:56.138 --> 05:58.532
Are we safe here?

05:58.662 --> 05:59.837
Why do you ask?

06:01.665 --> 06:04.233
The girl who died.

06:04.364 --> 06:07.367
Her mother said she was killed
by your cousin Stephen.

06:09.978 --> 06:11.936
[knocking]

06:16.898 --> 06:18.203
Good morning, Mr. Boone.

06:18.334 --> 06:19.727
Good morning.

06:19.857 --> 06:21.511
May I come in?

06:23.774 --> 06:24.819
Of course.

06:33.175 --> 06:36.004
Tane, please go
to your room now.

06:38.180 --> 06:41.052
- How's Mrs. Mallory today?
- In shock.

06:41.183 --> 06:44.665
Doctor Guilford attended
to her last night.

06:44.795 --> 06:46.014
Woman's husband is
still missing.

06:46.144 --> 06:48.146
Been three days now.

06:48.277 --> 06:50.497
He hasn't shown up for work.

06:53.195 --> 06:54.805
Is that why you're here?

06:54.936 --> 06:58.026
To look for Edward Mallory?

06:58.156 --> 07:00.768
I came to suggest
that you and your family

07:00.898 --> 07:03.814
stay out of Preacher's Corners,
even for a few days.

07:06.861 --> 07:08.428
Well, I have a business
to run.

07:10.212 --> 07:11.866
People will
assume we're hiding.

07:11.996 --> 07:13.868
It'll give
the wrong impression, sir.

07:13.998 --> 07:17.001
That may be, but you don't
have to, um,

07:17.132 --> 07:18.438
provoke people.

07:19.917 --> 07:22.703
My name provokes them!

07:27.229 --> 07:30.537
My children's skin
provokes them!

07:32.452 --> 07:34.018
I don't see much of a choice.

07:37.848 --> 07:38.980
You could go back from
where you came.

07:41.199 --> 07:43.724
Might I remind you
that you're in my house now.

07:47.336 --> 07:49.686
I'm sure you've heard of
my intent to build ships here.

07:49.817 --> 07:51.906
Hm.

07:52.036 --> 07:56.780
In two years, even
my detractors will thank me.

08:05.876 --> 08:08.270
Stay on my good side,
constable.

08:08.400 --> 08:10.794
I might even have
a job for you.

08:14.755 --> 08:15.886
Good day to you, sir.

08:18.933 --> 08:20.630
[door closes]

08:23.328 --> 08:29.160
Your constable thinks I should
take my family and leave.

08:29.291 --> 08:31.902
At the very least, to stay
out of town for a few days.

08:33.295 --> 08:36.298
Perhaps a day or two away
from school might be wise.

08:36.428 --> 08:38.256
We had nothing to do with
the death of that little girl.

08:38.387 --> 08:41.912
I know, I'm just...
[sighs]

08:42.043 --> 08:44.306
just think maybe to spare
the children

08:44.436 --> 08:45.786
some of the mean talk
that's bound to follow.

08:45.916 --> 08:47.004
Oh, my children can
handle mean talk.

08:47.135 --> 08:48.963
As you wish.

08:49.093 --> 08:51.313
And last night,

08:51.443 --> 08:54.142
I take it you put to rest
Rose Mallory's accusation?

09:01.149 --> 09:04.369
Perhaps this will be a
difficult day for the children.

09:04.500 --> 09:05.980
Would you escort them
to school, please?

09:06.110 --> 09:07.068
Of course.

09:11.942 --> 09:14.597
[insects buzzing,
horses neighing]

09:20.255 --> 09:23.214
What was it like
growing up here?

09:23.345 --> 09:27.392
Well, it was different
than it is now.

09:27.523 --> 09:31.005
When I was younger,
we used to run freely.

09:31.135 --> 09:34.008
I played in the woods
all the time.

09:34.138 --> 09:38.055
We didn't live
with the fear we do nowadays.

09:38.186 --> 09:41.145
Were the people mean to you
like they are to us?

09:41.276 --> 09:43.147
Yes and no.

09:43.278 --> 09:45.410
They were unpleasant.

09:45.541 --> 09:47.848
I didn't have many friends
when I was your age.

09:47.978 --> 09:50.198
- Why not?
- I was a little different.

09:50.328 --> 09:52.026
Kids made fun of me.

09:52.156 --> 09:54.289
Their parents thought
I had a big mouth.

09:54.419 --> 09:57.161
- You had opinions.
- That no one wanted to hear.

09:57.292 --> 09:59.337
You can't take
any of it personally.

09:59.468 --> 10:02.602
People always tear down
what they don't understand.

10:05.387 --> 10:08.085
[horse whinnies]

10:27.017 --> 10:28.628
[latch opening]

10:31.108 --> 10:32.632
Captain Boone.

10:34.416 --> 10:36.113
May I come in?

10:48.343 --> 10:50.693
Ask your questions, captain.

10:52.347 --> 10:54.654
I'll do my best to answer them.

10:57.439 --> 10:59.789
You say Stephen
hanged himself.

11:01.922 --> 11:03.140
Yes.

11:03.271 --> 11:05.229
And who told you that?

11:05.360 --> 11:07.971
I found the bodies myself.

11:08.102 --> 11:12.019
Both he and his daughter,
Marcella.

11:12.149 --> 11:13.194
I found the child first...

11:18.373 --> 11:20.157
...at the foot
of those cruel stairs.

11:25.249 --> 11:28.252
She was...

11:28.383 --> 11:30.690
cold and broken.

11:30.820 --> 11:32.822
A pair of scissors
pierced her throat.

11:39.263 --> 11:41.178
- I found Stephen next.
- [lamp rattles]

11:53.669 --> 11:56.846
- Did you attend their funeral?
- There was none.

11:58.195 --> 12:01.633
But there was a viewing.

12:01.764 --> 12:03.418
Phillip put the bodies
on display

12:03.548 --> 12:05.246
in the parlor for two days.

12:05.376 --> 12:07.335
The curious came,

12:07.465 --> 12:10.381
but it wasn't to pay respects.

12:10.512 --> 12:12.906
They were happy
to see Stephen dead.

12:14.255 --> 12:16.213
Why no funeral?

12:16.344 --> 12:18.563
On the third day when
I arrived, the bodies were gone.

12:18.694 --> 12:21.088
Phillip had buried his son
and granddaughter

12:21.218 --> 12:23.351
in the family plot.

12:23.481 --> 12:26.441
By then he was a broken man

12:26.571 --> 12:28.008
who rarely left his room.

12:30.445 --> 12:34.318
♪♪♪

12:34.449 --> 12:40.368
♪♪♪

12:40.498 --> 12:43.893
♪♪♪

12:44.024 --> 12:50.900
♪♪♪

12:51.031 --> 12:54.208
One week later...

12:54.338 --> 12:57.080
Phillip gave himself
to the sea.

13:02.085 --> 13:04.044
His body
was never recovered.

13:08.222 --> 13:12.269
You alone
witnessed both their deaths.

13:14.315 --> 13:15.272
No one else.

13:17.405 --> 13:18.928
That's right.

13:26.196 --> 13:27.284
Mrs. Cloris...

13:30.505 --> 13:32.855
I believe
you're hiding something.

13:37.120 --> 13:40.210
I believe Stephen is alive.

13:41.777 --> 13:43.126
[Charles grunts]

13:45.563 --> 13:49.219
Last night,
you know what I did?

13:52.179 --> 13:54.268
I opened Stephen's grave.

14:01.318 --> 14:03.233
Do you know what I found?

14:05.453 --> 14:07.107
Nothing.

14:09.457 --> 14:12.155
So how do you explain that?

14:16.203 --> 14:18.379
Now,

14:18.509 --> 14:23.166
I was lured here under
the pretense of an inheritance.

14:23.297 --> 14:25.168
To what end?

14:26.430 --> 14:27.431
I wouldn't know.

14:27.562 --> 14:29.346
You tell me what you do know!

14:32.306 --> 14:35.135
- Where is Stephen Boone?
- I couldn't say.

14:38.181 --> 14:39.487
Oh, I think you could.

14:41.358 --> 14:44.231
I beg you, leave me in peace.

14:50.411 --> 14:54.023
When you see my cousin,
you tell him.

14:55.459 --> 14:57.374
You tell him
I'm looking for him.

14:59.507 --> 15:01.422
And I will find him.

15:16.567 --> 15:19.309
[indistinct chatter]

15:27.187 --> 15:28.623
[coughing upstairs]

15:28.753 --> 15:31.278
- [weakly] George?
- Mary!

15:33.802 --> 15:35.064
- [flames crackling]
- Mary?

15:45.596 --> 15:47.424
Mary.

15:47.555 --> 15:49.122
What are you doing?

15:49.252 --> 15:51.167
I was cooking breakfast.

15:53.387 --> 15:55.084
I must've forgotten.

15:56.694 --> 15:58.392
I'm getting Doctor Guilford.

16:00.394 --> 16:01.612
[sighs]

16:01.743 --> 16:04.093
I think you should.

16:21.545 --> 16:22.546
[sighs]

16:26.681 --> 16:29.292
It's the illness, isn't it?

16:30.598 --> 16:32.556
George, I promise I will do

16:32.687 --> 16:35.559
everything in my power
to help Mary.

16:35.690 --> 16:38.388
We'll get through this.

16:38.519 --> 16:40.042
We will.

16:42.305 --> 16:43.567
Mary's tough.

16:45.961 --> 16:48.007
Make sure she rests.

16:49.660 --> 16:52.359
Add liver to her diet.

16:53.360 --> 16:55.318
I'll be back tonight
to bleed her,

16:55.449 --> 16:56.493
balance the humors.

17:13.554 --> 17:22.041
♪♪♪

17:27.437 --> 17:28.569
Martin.

17:31.528 --> 17:33.095
May I have a moment?

17:35.619 --> 17:37.317
Of course.

17:43.975 --> 17:47.196
They were taken from us
far too soon.

17:50.417 --> 17:53.072
Rose Mallory's accusations...

17:54.769 --> 17:58.338
...have the town talking.

17:58.468 --> 18:01.776
[chuckles]
That Stephen Boone is alive?

18:01.906 --> 18:04.431
That he's risen from the dead?

18:04.561 --> 18:07.303
I think we can be fairly certain
that that is not true.

18:08.609 --> 18:11.699
If our Lord could raise Lazarus,

18:11.829 --> 18:15.311
surely Satan could raise
Stephen Boone.

18:17.400 --> 18:19.098
I need to get back
to my sermon.

18:20.490 --> 18:22.362
For Susan Mallory's
funeral, hm?

18:22.492 --> 18:24.190
May I, uh, see it?

18:26.409 --> 18:28.324
You can hear it tomorrow.

18:28.455 --> 18:30.935
Are the Boones mentioned?

18:31.066 --> 18:33.416
Why would they be?

18:33.547 --> 18:36.463
The child died
from the Boone illness.

18:36.593 --> 18:39.901
You need to call it such.

18:40.031 --> 18:45.211
My job is to provide
comfort and hope.

18:46.429 --> 18:49.215
Not to spread hate.

18:51.695 --> 18:53.567
The people are frightened.
They feel helpless.

18:53.697 --> 18:56.004
Your job, Martin,

18:56.135 --> 18:59.486
is to put a face on that fear
so they can fight back.

18:59.616 --> 19:01.314
They need a scapegoat?

19:01.444 --> 19:03.533
They need a devil.

19:03.664 --> 19:06.493
I will have no part of that.

19:07.929 --> 19:10.845
Your own children,
my grandchildren,

19:10.975 --> 19:13.804
they were among the first
to die from the Boone pox.

19:13.935 --> 19:16.372
My Alice never recovered.

19:17.765 --> 19:20.159
Good day, Sam.

19:20.289 --> 19:22.987
This town needs you
to lead with strength.

19:23.118 --> 19:25.338
And conviction.

19:35.565 --> 19:37.611
Would you carry such hate
in your heart

19:37.741 --> 19:40.309
if Silence Boone hadn't bought
your father's land?

19:45.880 --> 19:50.450
She stole that land
from a drunkard.

19:53.975 --> 19:57.674
Deliver God's wrath
on the Boones tomorrow.

19:57.805 --> 20:00.547
Martin!

20:00.677 --> 20:02.766
Before it turns on you!

20:06.030 --> 20:08.772
[teacher] I'd like everyone
to memorize our 31 states,

20:08.903 --> 20:10.861
and be able to place them
on a map.

20:10.992 --> 20:13.386
You should know the capitals
too.

20:13.516 --> 20:17.085
[kids snickering]

20:17.216 --> 20:19.522
Is something wrong with the seat
I assigned you, Miss Boone?

20:19.653 --> 20:21.394
I couldn't hear you
from the back of the room.

20:21.524 --> 20:22.743
She's deaf as well as dark?

20:22.873 --> 20:24.875
That's enough, Mr. Knox!

20:25.006 --> 20:28.792
Today we keep that seat open,
in memory of Susan Mallory.

20:28.923 --> 20:31.360
You may take Penny Ashcroft's
seat but only till she returns.

20:31.491 --> 20:33.232
Miss Boone.

20:34.972 --> 20:36.539
Go ahead, Miss Boone.

20:44.504 --> 20:45.548
We've been expelled.

20:47.550 --> 20:49.683
There have been complaints.

20:49.813 --> 20:51.685
Parents are concerned
you may carry the illness.

20:55.210 --> 20:57.647
Everybody's talking about you
and the Boones.

20:57.778 --> 20:59.997
People are afraid, angry.

21:00.128 --> 21:02.130
I don't care
what people think.

21:02.261 --> 21:05.612
Finish your writing
and be done with Chapelwaite.

21:05.742 --> 21:07.396
Oh! I brought you something.

21:09.703 --> 21:10.747
What are these?

21:12.619 --> 21:14.925
Letters from Father
to Phillip Boone.

21:15.056 --> 21:16.840
I found them in the study
at Chapelwaite.

21:16.971 --> 21:18.668
Did you read them?

21:18.799 --> 21:20.975
I skimmed them.

21:21.105 --> 21:22.803
Were you aware that he was
still working for the Boones

21:22.933 --> 21:25.458
as recently as two years ago?

21:25.588 --> 21:27.721
No, I wasn't.

21:27.851 --> 21:30.811
He could've been here
in town on business.

21:30.941 --> 21:33.901
Oh, he had his second family.

21:34.031 --> 21:36.425
Until he abandoned them
as well.

21:36.556 --> 21:37.818
[chuckles]

21:37.948 --> 21:39.298
Oh.

21:52.006 --> 21:54.748
Unfair as it is,
I think it may be best

21:54.878 --> 21:57.185
if I home-school
the children for now.

21:57.316 --> 21:59.927
I'm not accustomed to backing
down so easily, Miss Morgan.

22:00.057 --> 22:02.930
Nor I,
but it's not us I worry about.

22:06.934 --> 22:09.937
Once the people get
to know you and the children

22:10.067 --> 22:12.548
and see that there's
nothing to fear,

22:12.679 --> 22:14.942
this animosity will diminish.

22:15.072 --> 22:17.597
Unless there is
something to fear.

22:23.037 --> 22:25.735
I believe my cousin Stephen
is alive.

22:27.868 --> 22:29.391
He's not.

22:30.784 --> 22:32.481
His grave is empty.

22:32.612 --> 22:34.570
Mr. Boone,

22:34.701 --> 22:37.878
I saw your cousin Stephen
dead

22:38.008 --> 22:41.534
along with Marcella
at their viewing

22:41.664 --> 22:43.536
in this very room.

22:44.972 --> 22:47.540
Then where's the body?

22:47.670 --> 22:49.063
Does it matter?

22:49.193 --> 22:51.631
Well, perhaps Phillip
buried him elsewhere

22:51.761 --> 22:54.024
for fear of grave robbers
or desecration.

22:54.155 --> 22:56.200
- I--[screams]
- [glass shatters]

22:56.331 --> 22:58.028
- [man outside] Go home!
- Down, down, down, down!

22:58.159 --> 23:00.553
[men yelling outside]

23:00.683 --> 23:01.902
Stay away from the windows!

23:02.032 --> 23:03.860
[glass shattering]

23:03.991 --> 23:06.036
Boone!

23:06.167 --> 23:07.560
Come out of that house!

23:07.690 --> 23:08.517
[Charles] Get down!

23:13.783 --> 23:16.046
Go find the children!
Honor!

23:16.177 --> 23:18.135
Keep everyone inside.

23:18.266 --> 23:19.876
[indistinct yelling outside]

23:20.007 --> 23:21.574
We're talking to you, Boone!

23:21.704 --> 23:24.054
- Go home!
- [indistinct yelling]

23:24.185 --> 23:24.794
- Get out of town!
- [gun cocks]

23:27.797 --> 23:30.017
Whoever throws the next rock
eats lead.

23:33.063 --> 23:34.587
Drop!

23:36.980 --> 23:38.504
Remove the hoods.

23:41.115 --> 23:42.029
You sons of bitches.

23:42.159 --> 23:43.422
[grunts]

23:48.383 --> 23:50.603
- [laughter]
- Not so tough now, eh, Boone?

23:50.733 --> 23:51.778
[grunts, moans]

23:53.736 --> 23:55.869
[indistinct chatter]

23:55.999 --> 23:57.566
[Charles grunts]

24:00.917 --> 24:01.875
[grunts]

24:05.922 --> 24:07.794
Get outta town, Boone!

24:07.924 --> 24:10.797
Take your shit and go!

24:10.927 --> 24:13.800
Nobody wants you here!

24:13.930 --> 24:16.063
Let me give you hand up,
Boone, huh?

24:16.193 --> 24:17.760
There we go.

24:17.891 --> 24:19.588
[gunshot]

24:28.684 --> 24:29.772
Get outta here!

24:32.732 --> 24:33.820
Now!

24:33.950 --> 24:35.735
This isn't over, Boone!

24:36.997 --> 24:39.913
[indistinct jeering]

24:40.043 --> 24:41.784
Oh, Charles!

24:48.008 --> 24:49.749
[grunts]

24:52.012 --> 24:53.840
[man gasps]

24:53.970 --> 24:55.755
I'm coming, I'm coming!

24:59.759 --> 25:01.978
[panting]

25:15.122 --> 25:16.819
Thompson!

25:17.951 --> 25:19.648
Mason!

25:30.790 --> 25:32.531
Thompson?

25:42.889 --> 25:48.677
[whip-poor-wills singing]

25:58.992 --> 26:00.820
[grunts]

26:00.950 --> 26:03.649
[blows landing, squelching]

26:09.089 --> 26:13.049
[breathing unsteadily]

26:13.180 --> 26:15.835
[groans, mumbles]

26:18.141 --> 26:20.143
[frightened gasps]

26:22.276 --> 26:26.759
[blood spattering]

26:33.504 --> 26:39.380
♪♪♪

26:39.510 --> 26:45.865
♪♪♪

27:35.262 --> 27:37.090
[exhales]

27:39.266 --> 27:40.702
How do you feel?

27:42.965 --> 27:44.837
Trampled by a horse.

27:44.967 --> 27:46.708
I found this in my cupboard.

27:46.839 --> 27:48.971
There are some medicaments
in here that might be useful.

27:51.060 --> 27:52.148
Thank you.

28:03.290 --> 28:05.031
May I?

28:06.597 --> 28:07.947
[sighs]

28:14.388 --> 28:16.042
[sucks air through teeth]

28:16.172 --> 28:17.696
[gasps in sympathy]

28:21.438 --> 28:22.918
- Is that all right?
- Mm-hmm.

28:35.104 --> 28:36.889
Stephen Boone.

28:37.019 --> 28:38.804
Toxic mercury.

28:38.934 --> 28:41.197
What is "F.I.H."?

28:41.328 --> 28:43.286
Frigate Island Hospital.

28:45.636 --> 28:47.813
Is it close?

28:48.901 --> 28:52.252
Mr. Boone,
you do not want to go there.

28:52.382 --> 28:54.080
It's a terrible place.

28:56.169 --> 28:57.866
Why is that?

28:59.346 --> 29:02.218
It's...an asylum.

29:04.133 --> 29:06.875
[Honor]
Father! Able is here!

29:17.059 --> 29:19.322
Good morning, Mr. Boone.

29:19.453 --> 29:20.759
Good morning.

29:23.109 --> 29:24.937
What brings you out so early?

29:25.067 --> 29:26.503
It's the mill.

29:26.634 --> 29:28.288
The men haven't shown for work.

29:35.469 --> 29:38.428
There was a young sailor
from Brighton!

29:38.559 --> 29:41.475
Who remarked to his girl,
"You've a tight one!"

29:41.605 --> 29:44.260
She replied, "Oh, my soul,

29:44.391 --> 29:46.349
"you're in the wrong hole!

29:46.480 --> 29:48.047
There's plenty of room
in the right one!"

29:48.177 --> 29:50.179
[men roaring with laughter]

30:03.192 --> 30:04.585
Well, you're new to town,
captain,

30:04.715 --> 30:08.197
so I'll fill you in
on the rules.

30:08.328 --> 30:12.288
His kind isn't allowed in here.

30:13.768 --> 30:15.814
We won't take long.

30:17.424 --> 30:18.425
[spits]

30:22.516 --> 30:24.474
Are you come down here
to buy us a round

30:24.605 --> 30:27.956
with all that Boone money
you inherited?

30:28.087 --> 30:29.392
[chortles]

30:29.523 --> 30:32.091
On the contrary.

30:32.221 --> 30:33.396
Well, it's evident
that none of you

30:33.527 --> 30:35.181
are concerned
with your jobs.

30:38.619 --> 30:40.577
So you're all fired.

30:40.708 --> 30:43.189
Well, that's awfully
kind of you

30:43.319 --> 30:45.321
to ride down here
and let us know.

30:48.368 --> 30:50.500
Any money that
you're owed

30:50.631 --> 30:52.241
will go toward
the repair of my windows.

30:55.157 --> 30:57.116
I don't understand.

30:58.639 --> 31:01.207
Listen; don't speak.

31:01.337 --> 31:03.122
Now, I pride myself on honesty.

31:05.776 --> 31:08.127
Now, you believe me
when I tell you

31:08.257 --> 31:10.303
that I will kill
every one of you...

31:12.435 --> 31:16.265
and I will burn
all your homes to the ground

31:16.396 --> 31:19.355
if you attempt any harm
against me or my family again.

31:21.314 --> 31:25.274
[stifled laugh]
You feel that, boys?

31:25.405 --> 31:29.017
A gust a hot air
just swept through the place.

31:29.148 --> 31:29.452
- [glass shatters]
- Aah!

31:30.889 --> 31:33.369
- [blow lands]
- [grunts]

31:33.500 --> 31:34.370
[grunts]

31:37.199 --> 31:39.027
You sit. Sit!

31:44.641 --> 31:47.906
Thompson, mark my words.

31:49.646 --> 31:51.910
I'm not one to play games.

32:05.532 --> 32:06.968
[spits]

32:11.451 --> 32:13.192
[groaning]

32:15.759 --> 32:18.719
Captain Boone, meet my
investor friends from Portland.

32:18.849 --> 32:21.330
They're gonna buy
your mill when you leave town

32:21.461 --> 32:23.942
or when it goes
out of business.

32:29.469 --> 32:31.340
I'll let your friend
over there tell you

32:31.471 --> 32:33.342
how I feel about the matter.

32:41.220 --> 32:46.790
♪♪♪

32:46.921 --> 32:50.707
[Rebecca] The Captain believes
that his cousin lives.

32:50.838 --> 32:55.103
By my own eyes and everything
I hold true, he is wrong.

32:56.931 --> 32:59.194
But why is that?

32:59.325 --> 33:00.500
How can I be certain?

33:03.503 --> 33:06.506
Is it so inconceivable
that the dead might rise?

33:06.636 --> 33:09.378
We acknowledge our soul
as separate from the body.

33:09.509 --> 33:11.990
One mortal and bound by time;

33:12.120 --> 33:15.689
the other immortal
and bound to nothing.

33:15.819 --> 33:20.433
The immortal soul is that
touch of God in each of us.

33:20.563 --> 33:23.566
It knows our maker
and His secrets.

33:26.700 --> 33:28.702
I can almost imagine,

33:28.832 --> 33:31.400
as the captain suggests,

33:31.531 --> 33:34.664
how one defiant soul,

33:34.795 --> 33:37.493
one lunatic Stephen Boone,

33:37.624 --> 33:41.323
might violate
the natural order,

33:41.454 --> 33:44.631
might will himself back
from the grave.

33:48.678 --> 33:50.115
[pounding on metal]

33:55.511 --> 33:57.296
I'm looking for Doctor Frost.

33:57.426 --> 33:59.124
I'm Doctor Frost.

33:59.254 --> 34:01.126
Who are you?

34:07.610 --> 34:08.611
[door closes]

34:10.657 --> 34:12.267
Charles Boone.

34:13.877 --> 34:16.228
Any relation to the Boones
of Chapelwaite?

34:17.577 --> 34:18.317
Yes.

34:19.927 --> 34:22.321
Those relations are
why I'm here.

34:25.628 --> 34:27.326
Walk with me.

34:32.809 --> 34:34.550
What troubles you,
Mr. Boone?

34:35.682 --> 34:37.771
Stephen Boone.

34:37.901 --> 34:40.208
- I'm looking for him.
- [distant screaming]

34:40.339 --> 34:43.429
[screaming]

34:43.559 --> 34:45.735
Well, you won't find him here.

34:45.866 --> 34:48.564
He should be six feet
beneath the ground.

34:48.695 --> 34:51.219
He should be.
He's not.

34:55.441 --> 34:57.356
You opened his grave?

34:57.486 --> 35:00.228
I did.

35:00.359 --> 35:03.231
[groaning]

35:07.540 --> 35:09.542
I'm curious.

35:09.672 --> 35:12.632
What motivated you
to exhume your cousin's grave?

35:13.937 --> 35:18.986
Two nights ago, a child
died in Preacher's Corners.

35:19.117 --> 35:20.770
The girl's mother swore

35:20.901 --> 35:23.469
that my cousin
Stephen was the killer.

35:23.599 --> 35:25.514
So you took it upon yourself

35:25.645 --> 35:27.473
to prove
that he was indeed dead.

35:27.603 --> 35:30.302
That's right.

35:30.432 --> 35:32.391
Yet there was no body.

35:34.088 --> 35:37.570
Now, there's been a history
of bad blood

35:37.700 --> 35:41.443
within my family
for many years.

35:41.574 --> 35:42.792
I'm beginning to believe
I've been drawn into it

35:42.923 --> 35:45.926
by my cousin.

35:46.056 --> 35:48.624
He's beginning to turn
the town against me.

35:50.757 --> 35:54.500
Mr. Boone, your reasoning
follows the pattern

35:54.630 --> 35:56.763
of classic persecution mania.

35:58.765 --> 36:01.289
No, Stephen Boone is alive.

36:05.641 --> 36:08.644
You're treating him yourself.

36:08.775 --> 36:10.603
Toxic mercury.

36:10.733 --> 36:12.909
For mania.

36:13.040 --> 36:16.478
I treated the whole family.

36:16.609 --> 36:19.351
They were each driven mad
by the same affliction.

36:20.917 --> 36:22.484
[man] No!

36:22.615 --> 36:24.617
No, no, no!

36:24.747 --> 36:26.793
Ice baths.

36:26.923 --> 36:30.188
Given to reduce
manic fits of agitation.

36:31.406 --> 36:36.368
[screaming]

36:36.498 --> 36:37.804
Your Grandmother Silence

36:37.934 --> 36:40.763
suffered terribly
from such fits.

36:40.894 --> 36:42.635
I treated her at Chapelwaite.

36:44.506 --> 36:48.336
[screaming continues]

36:49.990 --> 36:51.600
Is it the worms?

36:53.863 --> 36:55.865
You see them, don't you?

36:55.996 --> 36:59.652
The whole family saw them.

36:59.782 --> 37:04.657
An affliction
I coined vermiphobia...

37:06.006 --> 37:09.618
an obsessive fear of worms.

37:09.749 --> 37:14.971
Silence, Stephen, and Phillip
were all driven mad by them.

37:15.102 --> 37:19.976
They believed they could cure
their madness with a book,

37:20.107 --> 37:23.415
a sacred book of forbidden
rites or some such nonsense,

37:23.545 --> 37:25.460
but there is no book.

37:25.591 --> 37:27.767
And there's no cure.

37:30.204 --> 37:32.337
I'm not mad, Doctor.

37:32.467 --> 37:34.252
It's hereditary.

37:35.818 --> 37:38.865
The visions
will only get worse.

37:38.995 --> 37:42.390
They'll become all-consuming,

37:42.521 --> 37:45.524
leaving nothing left of you.

37:46.829 --> 37:50.833
Check yourself into this place
while you can, Mr. Boone,

37:50.964 --> 37:53.749
for your own self
and all those around you.

37:53.880 --> 37:55.403
Stephen!

37:56.883 --> 37:58.624
Stephen!

37:58.754 --> 38:00.408
He's not Stephen, dear.

38:00.539 --> 38:02.280
[Charles] Sorry. No.

38:05.761 --> 38:06.806
Stephen!

38:07.937 --> 38:09.287
Stephen!

38:10.592 --> 38:12.681
[sobs] Stephen!

38:24.737 --> 38:25.868
There she blows!

38:25.999 --> 38:27.696
He's going to sound!

38:29.045 --> 38:30.743
In stunsails.

38:30.873 --> 38:32.484
Down topgallants.

38:32.614 --> 38:34.834
Stand by, three boats!

38:34.964 --> 38:37.053
Get those lines ready,
Mr. Bones.

38:37.184 --> 38:39.578
Be sure they're fast
to the irons.

38:42.929 --> 38:45.671
[flies buzzing]

38:55.942 --> 38:57.726
[horse neighs]

38:59.902 --> 39:01.643
Ahoy there.

39:05.865 --> 39:08.650
Whatcha doin' up there?

39:08.781 --> 39:10.913
Looking for whales.

39:11.044 --> 39:13.351
Better you should look
for the book.

39:14.830 --> 39:15.831
What book?

39:20.923 --> 39:21.968
What's your name?

39:22.098 --> 39:23.839
Tane.

39:23.970 --> 39:25.406
What's yours?

39:26.929 --> 39:28.409
[woman chuckles]

39:31.151 --> 39:32.848
I have no name.

39:34.633 --> 39:36.635
Everyone has a name.

39:36.765 --> 39:38.463
Not us.

39:38.593 --> 39:40.029
We renounced ours.

39:40.160 --> 39:42.641
Our God doesn't allow it.

39:44.773 --> 39:47.559
Doesn't allow
a Christian name?

39:47.689 --> 39:49.561
[scoffs]

39:49.691 --> 39:52.781
Our god is older than yours.

39:52.912 --> 39:57.133
No arms, no legs,
no hands, no feet.

39:57.264 --> 40:00.833
It burrows the earth,
hunting for meat.

40:00.963 --> 40:02.704
No nose, no ears.

40:02.835 --> 40:05.359
No eyes, no head.

40:05.490 --> 40:07.709
It squirms in the grave,
eating the dead.

40:07.840 --> 40:09.058
Stop it!

40:09.189 --> 40:10.843
No arms, no legs!

40:10.973 --> 40:12.845
No hands, no feet!

40:12.975 --> 40:15.587
It burrows the earth,
hunting for meat.

40:15.717 --> 40:16.762
No nose, no ears.

40:16.892 --> 40:18.720
No eyes, no head.

40:18.851 --> 40:20.592
It squirms in the grave,
eating the dead!

40:20.722 --> 40:22.028
Stop it! Go away!

40:22.158 --> 40:24.465
Tell your father
to find the book!

40:33.039 --> 40:34.606
[screams]

40:51.057 --> 40:52.972
Good evenin', Mr. Boone.

40:53.102 --> 40:54.930
My work is done here.

40:55.061 --> 40:57.193
Crazy as it sounds,

40:57.324 --> 40:59.979
there's not a rat to be found
in or around the place.

41:05.027 --> 41:07.465
I trust you, Mr. Fletcher.

41:08.944 --> 41:10.598
Thank you for your help.

41:30.183 --> 41:32.881
You found your necklace.

41:33.012 --> 41:34.622
I told you
I didn't take her shells.

41:37.407 --> 41:39.105
Father!

41:39.235 --> 41:41.586
- Evening, Mr. Boone.
- Able.

41:43.892 --> 41:46.678
- Father?
- Yes?

41:46.808 --> 41:50.682
A strange girl gave me an apple,

41:50.812 --> 41:52.161
and there were worms in it.

41:52.292 --> 41:54.294
She came into the barn,

41:54.424 --> 41:55.991
and she said something
about a book.

41:59.908 --> 42:01.127
Worms?

42:05.000 --> 42:06.959
You saw them?

42:07.089 --> 42:09.091
I did.

42:09.222 --> 42:11.616
Did anyone else see this?

42:11.746 --> 42:12.878
Honor?

42:13.008 --> 42:15.097
Loa?

42:15.228 --> 42:16.882
You believe me, don't you?

42:22.278 --> 42:23.845
I do.

42:26.108 --> 42:27.806
I do believe you.

42:32.854 --> 42:36.641
I'm sorry;
it's been a long day.

42:36.771 --> 42:38.294
I, uh...

42:38.425 --> 42:40.819
I won't be joining you
for dinner.

42:40.949 --> 42:44.039
[receding steps]

42:52.787 --> 42:54.746
Mr. Boone.

42:56.095 --> 42:58.967
Your trip to Frigate Island;
did you find anything?

43:01.187 --> 43:03.581
More than I bargained for.

43:05.321 --> 43:07.106
Goodnight, Rebecca.

43:13.329 --> 43:20.946
♪♪♪

43:21.076 --> 43:28.954
♪♪♪

43:29.084 --> 43:35.961
♪♪♪

43:36.091 --> 43:41.009
♪♪♪

43:43.316 --> 43:45.100
Father thinks highly of you.

43:45.231 --> 43:47.189
He's a good man.

43:47.320 --> 43:49.235
I haven't met many like him.

43:49.365 --> 43:50.932
Do you think he misses
the ocean?

43:51.063 --> 43:52.891
I think so.

43:53.021 --> 43:54.936
He's more comfortable out there.

43:55.067 --> 43:56.895
What about you?

43:59.941 --> 44:01.029
I like it here.

44:04.119 --> 44:05.904
Well, I'm glad you're here.

44:09.255 --> 44:10.169
[kiss]

44:16.262 --> 44:17.872
I'd better go.

44:18.003 --> 44:19.178
I'm sorry.
Did I offend you?

44:19.308 --> 44:21.789
No.
Not at all.

44:24.139 --> 44:26.054
Goodnight, Honor.

44:33.975 --> 44:38.763
[crickets chirping]

45:00.132 --> 45:01.699
Stop.

45:07.182 --> 45:09.881
I beg of you. Stop it.

45:12.361 --> 45:14.059
There are no rats.

45:16.322 --> 45:17.845
There are no...

45:23.024 --> 45:24.852
There are no rats!

45:28.160 --> 45:30.249
[scuffling, creaking]

45:30.379 --> 45:31.859
There are no rats.

45:33.687 --> 45:37.343
[loud scuffling]

45:37.473 --> 45:39.258
There are no rats!

45:47.135 --> 45:49.224
[grunts]

45:49.355 --> 45:52.010
- [grunts]
- [rattling continues]

45:55.100 --> 45:58.451
- There are no rats!
- [axe chopping]

45:58.581 --> 46:00.975
[thumps, Charles shouting]

46:05.023 --> 46:07.939
[ceiling creaks]

46:08.069 --> 46:10.245
[distant shouting, crashes]

46:13.379 --> 46:15.033
What is that?

46:15.163 --> 46:16.251
I'm not sure.

46:21.039 --> 46:23.345
[shouting, grunting]

46:31.397 --> 46:32.398
- [shouts]
- [screams]

46:32.528 --> 46:33.965
Charles, no!

46:35.357 --> 46:36.968
Father,
what's wrong with you?

46:38.534 --> 46:40.972
Come, children.
Everyone upstairs.

46:41.102 --> 46:42.364
Everyone upstairs.

46:53.288 --> 46:57.945
[distant chopping, splashes]

47:12.394 --> 47:15.223
[shuddering]

47:17.399 --> 47:19.227
[exhales deeply]

47:27.540 --> 47:30.325
[labored breathing]

47:51.520 --> 47:53.044
[gasps for air]
